Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.05,0:00:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You and I make a lot of decisions every day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.75,0:00:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, some have a little impact on our lives; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.56,0:00:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,others have a very big impact. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.23,0:00:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can appreciate that we can make \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.46,0:00:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,choices and decisions for ourselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.30,0:00:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of how life would be \Nif you made no decisions for yourself\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.97,0:00:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,—someone tells you when to go to bed,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.84,0:00:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,they pick out your clothes, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.84,0:00:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and they tell you what to do for work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.84,0:00:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, none of us would like that!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.74,0:00:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah gave each of us free will, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.31,0:00:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s the precious gift \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.42,0:00:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of making choices for ourselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.92,0:00:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, have you ever thought \Nabout why Jehovah gave us this gift? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.22,0:00:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, \Nwhy trust us with free will \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.99,0:00:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,when he knew that we could make \Nbad choices or decisions? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.90,0:00:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, one powerful reason is love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.03,0:00:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The only way to give us the gift of love \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.24,0:00:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is also to give us the gift of free will. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.17,0:00:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The two are tied together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.24,0:01:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You really can’t have \None without the other.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.91,0:01:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \Nif I programmed my computer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.88,0:01:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to give me a message \Nevery day at 2:00 p.m.: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.35,0:01:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“John, I love you. \NI think you’re a wonderful guy,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.42,0:01:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I think there’d be a little something \Nwrong with me if I thought: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.79,0:01:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Aw, isn’t that nice? \NMy computer, it loves me.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.56,0:01:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, love only exists \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.00,0:01:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,if it comes truly \Nfrom a free-will expression.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.33,0:01:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, did Jehovah place \Nany boundaries on free will? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.47,0:01:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.24,0:01:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They were stated in the Law \Nto the nation of Israel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.98,0:01:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jesus later repeated them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.64,0:01:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,at Matthew 22:37-40: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.08,0:01:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“He said to him: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.65,0:01:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘“You must love Jehovah your God \Nwith your whole heart \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.32,0:01:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘“and with your whole soul\Nand with your whole mind.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.86,0:01:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘This is the greatest\Nand first commandment.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.96,0:01:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘The second, like it, is this: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.27,0:01:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘“You must love your\Nneighbor as yourself.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.27,0:02:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘On these two commandments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.97,0:02:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole Law hangs,\Nand the Prophets.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.54,0:02:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So our use of free will \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.44,0:02:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,has love of God\Nand love of neighbor \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.18,0:02:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,as its boundaries.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.18,0:02:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice, for example, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.18,0:02:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,what people are doing \Nin this picture, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.65,0:02:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,both inside the circle boundary \Nand outside. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.66,0:02:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,See, free will allows us to do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.73,0:02:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,any of the things \Nwe see in the picture. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.83,0:02:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But love of God \Nand love of neighbor \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.87,0:02:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,move us to reject \Nwhat’s outside the circle \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.53,0:02:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and choose \Nto do the kinds of things \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.57,0:02:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that we see inside the circle.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.04,0:02:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, to stay \Nwithin those boundaries, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.04,0:02:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah gave us \Na marvelous brain \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.21,0:02:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and a built-in conscience, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.38,0:02:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,but he also knows \Nwe need more help. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.75,0:02:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s why \Nhe also gave us Bible principles\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.99,0:02:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,—basic truths from the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.06,0:02:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that can help us \Nto make good decisions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.72,0:02:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And it can safely be said \Nthat any decision we face \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.36,0:03:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,can be guided \Nby Bible principles. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.70,0:03:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, our Creator, Jehovah, \Nknows what’s best for us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.50,0:03:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And he also trusts us \Nto make decisions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.84,0:03:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,based on Bible principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.24,0:03:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because he knows \Nthat when we do that, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.58,0:03:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,then we’re really, \Ntruly going to be happy, content, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.95,0:03:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and at peace with him \Nand with others.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.45,0:03:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So in review so far: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.55,0:03:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah gave us free will\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.95,0:03:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,—that’s the privilege \Nto make choices for ourselves—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.42,0:03:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and he also gave us \NBible principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.86,0:03:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,as the boundaries \Nto our choices. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.80,0:03:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But making difficult decisions \Nrequires that we train ourselves \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.34,0:03:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to recognize Bible principles \Nand apply them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.67,0:03:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s read Romans 12:1, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.91,0:03:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and let’s see how this verse \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.98,0:03:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,describes the decision-making process. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.45,0:03:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“Therefore, I appeal to you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.45,0:04:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“by the compassions of God, brothers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.46,0:04:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“to present your bodies \Nas a living sacrifice, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.99,0:04:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“holy and acceptable to God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.73,0:04:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,a sacred service \Nwith your power of reason.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.73,0:04:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So are we using \Nour “power of reason” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.24,0:04:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand Bible principles? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.58,0:04:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, young children \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.71,0:04:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,ask lots of questions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.11,0:04:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But has a child ever asked you: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.25,0:04:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“What happens when I drop a ball? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.42,0:04:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,a pencil? a book?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.89,0:04:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they don’t ask that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.89,0:04:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They know what happens \Nto anything they drop. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.46,0:04:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It falls down! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.46,0:04:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the child doesn’t need \Nrules for every object \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.46,0:04:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but has quickly grasped the principle. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.47,0:04:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything he drops falls down. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.14,0:04:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, \Nwhat if an 18-year-old asked you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.97,0:04:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“What’s going to happen\Nwhen I drop this pen?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.74,0:04:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it’s obvious \Nhe’s not been paying attention \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.88,0:04:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to basic principles of life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.78,0:05:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So by us paying attention \Nto Bible principles, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.69,0:05:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,we can very quickly see \Nthe pattern \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.82,0:05:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of love of God \Nand love of neighbor \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.16,0:05:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and know \Nthe right thing to do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.40,0:05:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,without a long list of rules \Nfor every situation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.87,0:05:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how can we train\Nour “power of reason”?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.34,0:05:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We train it by paying attention \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.81,0:05:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,as we read and study the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.71,0:05:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we don’t need rules \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.75,0:05:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,for which movies to watch, \Nwhich songs to listen to, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.28,0:05:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,or what clothes we can wear. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.52,0:05:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If we’re paying attention \Nwhen we’re reading the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.72,0:05:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,we train our conscience \Nwith Bible principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.23,0:05:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,so we can make \Nsuch decisions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.36,0:05:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,without needing \Na long list of rules. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.66,0:05:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, \Nwe could compare our training \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.13,0:05:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of our “power of reason” \Nto a blind person \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.34,0:05:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,using a guide dog. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.51,0:05:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, an untrained dog \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.51,0:06:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,would be very helpful \Nto a blind person. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.21,0:06:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It would bark when others \Nwere around, for example. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.71,0:06:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,However, \Na dog trained \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.95,0:06:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in specific skills \Nis amazingly helpful. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.55,0:06:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The dog knows \Nwhen to stop at curbs \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.96,0:06:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and walk around obstacles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.96,0:06:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that the person \Nmight run their head into. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.43,0:06:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,A guide dog \Nis also taught a skill called \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.16,0:06:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“intelligent disobedience.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.67,0:06:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if the blind person \Nencourages the dog forward, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.10,0:06:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it won’t obey, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.11,0:06:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but it’ll pull \Nthe person back from danger. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.97,0:06:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it can take a year or more \Nof training for the dog to learn \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.85,0:06:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the amazing skills \Nthat are so helpful to a blind person.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.95,0:06:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Likewise, our raw, \Nuntrained “power of reason” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.09,0:06:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,can help us to a degree. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.12,0:06:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it can be amazing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.16,0:06:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,if we take the time to train it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.16,0:06:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, here are \Nthree skills that we can use \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.16,0:06:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to train our “power of reason.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.17,0:06:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They are illustrating, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.50,0:07:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,analyzing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.50,0:07:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and balancing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.17,0:07:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, to consider our first skill, \Nillustrating, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.08,0:07:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s use the general topic \Nof forgiveness.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.15,0:07:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What Bible principles \Ncould help with forgiveness? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.29,0:07:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Please think of as many principles \Nand scriptures as you can. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.49,0:07:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if it helps, \Nyou can pause the program now \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.86,0:07:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and write down \Nthe principles that come to mind. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.37,0:07:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, your list \Nmay include principles like these: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.40,0:07:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew 18:22 says \Nto forgive “up to 77 times”; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.44,0:07:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 12:18 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.91,0:07:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“The tongue of the wise is a healing”; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.92,0:07:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and Colossians 3:13 tells us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.42,0:07:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to ‘forgive one another freely.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.79,0:07:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the skill \Nwe want to learn is illustrating\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.96,0:08:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,—creating a mental picture \Nof an idea or principle \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.10,0:08:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to see its real meaning \Nand impact. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.20,0:08:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, even if we \Nare not skilled artists, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.17,0:08:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,all of us can and do create \Npictures in our minds. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.17,0:08:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,When illustrating, \Npay attention to things that are similar \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.84,0:08:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,or like the thing \Nyou are trying to visualize. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.91,0:08:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \Nif sin is like debt, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.92,0:08:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,then forgiveness \Nis like someone canceling the debt. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.59,0:08:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If a hurtful remark \Nis like a cut, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.89,0:08:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,then forgiveness \Nis like seeing it heal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.73,0:08:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If sin is like a mark \Non a blackboard, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.27,0:08:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,forgiveness is like erasing it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.60,0:08:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 12:18 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.87,0:08:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is a great example \Nof using the “like” technique. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.28,0:08:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“Thoughtless speech \Nis like the stabs of a sword, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.35,0:08:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but the tongue of the wise \Nis a healing.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.85,0:09:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine what your skin \Nwould look like \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.86,0:09:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,if you still had \Nevery open cut, bruise, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.06,0:09:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,or bleeding scratch \Nsince childhood. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.56,0:09:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,See, Jehovah \Nwonderfully designed our body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.43,0:09:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to heal such minor cuts \Nand bruises. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.20,0:09:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can now visualize \Nhow the forgiveness of others \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.27,0:09:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,helps us to heal emotionally. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.84,0:09:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, learning to illustrate, \Nor visualize, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.21,0:09:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,takes time and practice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.21,0:09:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it can be one \Nof the most powerful skills we use \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.62,0:09:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to train \Nour “power of reason,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.78,0:09:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and it can also be \Nquite enjoyable. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.02,0:09:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, \Ntry at your family worship \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.12,0:09:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to take \Nthe principles for a topic \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.59,0:09:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and see \Nhow many similarities, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.89,0:09:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,or “likes,” \Nyou can come up with. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.23,0:09:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, granted, \Nthey all won’t be amazing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.00,0:09:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but you may be surprised \Nby the insights \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.07,0:09:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that come from seeing \Nsomething from a new perspective.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.11,0:09:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s consider now \Nour second skill: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.58,0:09:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,analyzing.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.68,0:09:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, analyzing something means \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.95,0:09:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“examining it carefully in detail.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.82,0:10:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And let’s use \Nthe topic of wrong desires. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.32,0:10:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in this case, \Nlet’s say that we’ve already found \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.19,0:10:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the principle \Nat Colossians 3:5: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.23,0:10:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“Deaden, therefore, your body members \Nthat are on the earth \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.90,0:10:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“as respects sexual immorality, \Nuncleanness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.50,0:10:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“uncontrolled sexual passion, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.87,0:10:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“hurtful desire, and greediness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.37,0:10:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,which is idolatry.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.88,0:10:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what can we learn\Nfrom analyzing Colossians 3:5\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.78,0:10:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to help when we struggle \Nwith wrong desires? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.95,0:10:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, feel free \Nto pause the program \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.75,0:10:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if you want some time \Nto think about it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.53,0:10:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Look carefully \Nat each step outlined. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.06,0:10:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice, for example, \Nwhat appears to be \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.07,0:10:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,a reverse order \Nof the steps leading to sin? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.90,0:10:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This verse works its way \Nfrom sexual immorality \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.64,0:11:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,back to the very roots \Nof the problem.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.24,0:11:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let’s take each phrase \Nstarting with the last, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.51,0:11:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“greediness, which is idolatry.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.35,0:11:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, sexual immorality \Nstarts with selfishness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.55,0:11:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,greedily putting our needs \Nahead of anything else. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.06,0:11:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Next is “hurtful desire.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.23,0:11:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Greediness leads to “hurtful desire.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.80,0:11:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s like a person \Nhanging around a bakery, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.97,0:11:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,smelling the bread and cakes \Nwhen he can’t pay for it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.47,0:11:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Likewise, \Nhanging around immoral entertainment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.84,0:11:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,or bad associates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.84,0:11:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,can feed “hurtful desire” \Nfor what is not ours. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.35,0:11:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Next is listed \N“uncontrolled sexual passion.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.85,0:11:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So “hurtful desire” \Nhas now turned from an idea \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.36,0:11:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,into a strong emotion \Nof passion, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.36,0:11:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,causing one \Nto look for an opportunity \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.86,0:11:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to fulfill the desire. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.53,0:11:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, “uncleanness.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.27,0:12:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The previous steps have now led \Nto inappropriate physical conduct \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.57,0:12:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,with another person. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.81,0:12:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, “sexual immorality”\N—serious sin. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.55,0:12:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Sexual immorality \Nhas occurred between persons \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.45,0:12:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that are not married \Nto one another. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.42,0:12:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So analyzing Colossians 3:5 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.49,0:12:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,can really help us to eliminate, \Nnot stimulate, wrong desires. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.39,0:12:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can see \Nhow important it is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.86,0:12:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to get rid \Nof wrong desires immediately. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.40,0:12:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s easier \Nto walk away from sin \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.40,0:12:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,when we’re still in the early stages, \Nrather than later.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.94,0:12:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So we need \Nto practice the skill \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.11,0:12:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,of not simply \Njust reading scriptures \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.41,0:12:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,but analyzing them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.41,0:12:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,until we’ve learned \Nall that we can. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.58,0:12:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can use \Nthe many research tools we have \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.92,0:12:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to find valuable comments \Nand application.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.82,0:12:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let’s consider our third \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.79,0:12:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and final skill: balancing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.93,0:12:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And to do that, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.93,0:13:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s use a question \Non the topic of alcohol.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.47,0:13:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What Bible principles \Ncould help a couple to decide \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.70,0:13:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,whether to serve alcohol \Nat their wedding? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.31,0:13:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What principles and scriptures \Ndo you think would help them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.08,0:13:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,make a balanced decision? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.18,0:13:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, you’re welcome \Nto pause the program \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.48,0:13:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,if you’d like to write down \Nwhat comes to mind \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.85,0:13:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,or to research something. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.65,0:13:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, your list probably has \Nsome of these principles. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.52,0:13:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,At John 2:9, \NJesus made wine for a wedding. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.36,0:13:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,However, \N1 Corinthians 6:10 says \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.17,0:13:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that ‘drunkards \Nwill not inherit the Kingdom.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.54,0:13:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And 1 Corinthians 10:31, 32 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.27,0:13:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“Whether you are eating or drinking . . . , \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.94,0:13:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,do all things for God’s glory” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.45,0:13:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and to “keep from becoming \Ncauses for stumbling.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.85,0:13:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, \Nit doesn’t seem \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.85,0:13:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that any one principle \Nprovides the answer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.49,0:14:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The couple could simply say: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.49,0:14:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“Well, Jesus served wine at a wedding, \Nso we can too.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.13,0:14:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,However, there’s really more \Nto it than that, isn’t there? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.03,0:14:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s clear that a balance \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.70,0:14:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of all these Bible principles \Nis needed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.57,0:14:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Will relatives \Nor others be there \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.27,0:14:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,who might be prone \Nto overdrinking? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.87,0:14:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Would serving alcohol bother \Nthe conscience of many present \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.71,0:14:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because of local customs \Nand feelings about alcohol? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.88,0:14:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s often the case \Nwhen making decisions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.72,0:14:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that we need to balance \Nseveral Bible principles, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.46,0:14:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,not taking any one principle solely \Non its own merit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.23,0:14:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah expects us \Nto use our “power of reason” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.10,0:14:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to balance Bible principles \Nand make good decisions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.37,0:14:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Ecclesiastes 7:16-18 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.01,0:14:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,gives us good advice \Nabout being balanced. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.98,0:14:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not be overly righteous, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.28,0:15:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“nor show yourself excessively wise. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.32,0:15:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“Why should you bring ruin to yourself? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.99,0:15:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not be excessively wicked, \Nnor be foolish. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.19,0:15:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“Why should you die before your time? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.32,0:15:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“It is best to grasp one warning \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.36,0:15:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“without letting go of the other; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.36,0:15:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,for the one who fears God \Nwill heed them both.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.27,0:15:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,How true. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.37,0:15:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Such balance between extremes \Nis often necessary \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.81,0:15:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,when we apply \NBible principles. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.87,0:15:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to heed them both, \Nso to speak. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.81,0:15:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to balance \Nall the Bible principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.25,0:15:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,so we can come \Nto the decision \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.25,0:15:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that would show love of God \Nand love of neighbor. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.75,0:15:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We could illustrate the balance \Nbetween different Bible principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.09,0:15:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and applying them with this model bike. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.96,0:15:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a gift from a brother in Malawi. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.33,0:15:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, a bicycle has \Nthree basic principles of operation: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.50,0:15:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the brakes, the pedals, and the steering. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.57,0:15:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the brakes are really like principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.11,0:15:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that slow us down \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.11,0:16:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,or stop us from doing the wrong thing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.24,0:16:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And the pedals are really like the principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.45,0:16:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that move us forward \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.45,0:16:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in showing love for Jehovah \Nand our brothers and sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.42,0:16:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And the steering is like our free will \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.55,0:16:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to choose a direction in life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.19,0:16:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that pleases Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.19,0:16:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So making decisions \Nis like riding a bicycle. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.26,0:16:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to balance \Nseveral Bible principles.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.30,0:16:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So in review, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.47,0:16:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah gave us free will \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.84,0:16:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to use within the boundaries \Nof love of God and love of neighbor \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.37,0:16:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and many other fine Bible principles. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.28,0:16:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Making difficult decisions requires \Nthat we train our “power of reason” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.18,0:16:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to recognize Bible principles \Nand apply them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.95,0:16:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And we discussed \Nhow to train \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.99,0:16:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,our power of reason \Nwith the three skills: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.16,0:16:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,illustrating, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.59,0:16:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,analyzing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.86,0:16:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and balancing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.23,0:16:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So no matter what decisions \Nyou are faced with, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.30,0:16:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we encourage you: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.30,0:16:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let Bible principles guide you.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.42,0:00:06.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは毎日\Nたくさんの決定をします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.32,0:00:10.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,小さな決定もあれば\N大きな決定もあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.99,0:00:14.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分で選択し\N決定できることに感謝できます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.66,0:00:19.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,もし自分で決定できないとしたら\Nと考えてみてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.30,0:00:22.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつ寝るか 何を着るか\Nどんな仕事をするかを—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.97,0:00:25.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,だれかに決められる\Nとしたらどうでしょう？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.74,0:00:28.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,だれもそうなりたいとは思いません！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.58,0:00:30.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは自分で決定ができるよう—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.88,0:00:35.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,自由意志という素晴らしい贈り物を\N与えてくださいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.39,0:00:39.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがこの贈り物を与えてくださった\N理由を考えたことがありますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.79,0:00:43.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちが時に良くない選択や\N決定をしてしまうのに—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.19,0:00:46.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちを信頼して\N与えてくださったのはなぜでしょう？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.63,0:00:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,1つの大切な理由は 愛です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.00,0:00:55.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちに愛を贈る唯一の手段が\N自由意志という贈り物なのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.57,0:00:57.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,この2つは密接に関連しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.97,0:01:00.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,片方だけでは成り立ちません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.74,0:01:04.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば わたしが自分に \N“ジョン 愛しています”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.15,0:01:06.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなたは素晴らしい人です”\N というメールを—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.78,0:01:09.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,毎日午後2時に送るよう\Nセットしたとします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.99,0:01:12.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,それを見て “ああ ありがたい”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.42,0:01:16.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“コンピューターがわたしを愛している”\N とは考えません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.79,0:01:23.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうです 愛とは自由意志からのみ\N出てくるものなのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.97,0:01:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,では エホバは自由意志に\N制限を設けられましたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.20,0:01:33.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,はい そのことをイスラエル国民への\N律法の中に記されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.28,0:01:40.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,後にイエスは マタイ 22章37-40節で\Nそのことに言及されました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.28,0:01:46.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,“イエスは彼に言われた\N「『あなたは 心をこめ 魂をこめ—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.29,0:01:49.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,思いをこめてあなたの神\Nエホバを愛さねばならない』”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.93,0:01:55.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,“これが最大で第一のおきてです\N 第二もそれと同様であって こうです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.70,0:01:59.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,“『あなたは隣人を自分自身のように\N 愛さねばならない』”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.34,0:02:02.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,“律法全体はこの二つのおきてに\N かかっており—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.74,0:02:05.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,“預言者たちもまたそうです」”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.64,0:02:07.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちの自由意志は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.34,0:02:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,神と隣人への愛という境界内で\N示されるべきです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.05,0:02:15.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば この絵の中で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.42,0:02:22.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,円の境界内にいる人と\N外にいる人との違いに注目してください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.69,0:02:26.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,自由意志を用いて\N絵の中にいる人は何でもできます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.53,0:02:32.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 神と隣人への愛は\Nわたしたちを円の外にいる人から遠ざけ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.07,0:02:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,円の中にいる人に\N良いことを行なうよう動かします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.37,0:02:42.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,円の中にいるために エホバは貴重な\N知力と良心を与えてくださいましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.85,0:02:46.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,同時に助けが必要であることも\Nご存じです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.72,0:02:52.19,Default2,,0,0,0,,だからこそ エホバは聖書の原則を与えて\Nその基本的な真理によって—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.19,0:02:55.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,良い決定ができるように\Nしてくださいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.69,0:03:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それで どんな決定も\N聖書の原則を導きにできるのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.70,0:03:06.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,創造者エホバは何が最善かをご存じです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.20,0:03:11.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちが聖書の原則によって決定すると\N信頼してくださっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.74,0:03:15.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうするなら\Nわたしたちが幸福になり 満足し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.65,0:03:20.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,神と隣人との平和な関係を\N楽しめることをご存じなのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.18,0:03:22.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,振り返ってみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.75,0:03:25.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは自由意志を\N与えてくださいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.69,0:03:29.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは 決定をする上での貴重な贈り物です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.23,0:03:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,また 決定に制限を設けるため\N聖書の原則も与えてくださいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.80,0:03:39.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,難しい決定をする時には—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.40,0:03:45.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,特に聖書の原則を認め\N当てはめなければなりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.84,0:03:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ローマ 12章1節を読んで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.91,0:03:55.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,決定することに関して\N何と述べているか考えてみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.25,0:03:58.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,“そのようなわけで 兄弟たち—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.35,0:04:01.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしは神の情けによって\N あなた方に懇願します”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.96,0:04:05.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなた方の体を\N 神に受け入れられる—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.03,0:04:08.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,“生きた 聖なる犠牲として\N 差し出しなさい”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.06,0:04:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“これがあなた方の\N 理性による神聖な奉仕です”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.40,0:04:19.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の原則を理解するため\N“理性”を働かせていますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.38,0:04:24.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば\N子どもはたくさんの質問をします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.51,0:04:26.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも こう聞いたりするでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.48,0:04:31.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ボールを離したらどうなるの？\Nペンは？本は？”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.42,0:04:32.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,そんなことはしません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.92,0:04:35.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,物を離したらどうなるかは\N分かっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.63,0:04:37.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,当然落ちます！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.59,0:04:43.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,子どもは原則を理解したなら\N規則など必要とはしません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.67,0:04:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,手から放した物は落ちます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.00,0:04:51.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 18歳の子が\N“このペンを離したらどうなるの？”—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.11,0:04:54.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,と聞いたならどうでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.64,0:04:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,明らかに物理の基本原則を\N理解していないことになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.55,0:05:04.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の原則に注意を払うなら—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.79,0:05:09.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,長い規則集など必要とせずに\N正しいことを見分け—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.43,0:05:16.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,神と隣人への愛を示す方法を\Nすぐに見極めることができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.37,0:05:22.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,では どのように\N“理性”を働かせますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.61,0:05:28.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を注意深く読み \N研究することによってそうできます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.64,0:05:31.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな映画を観るか \Nどんな音楽を聴くか—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.95,0:05:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,何を着るかに関して\N規則は必要ありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.42,0:05:42.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書を注意深く読むなら\N聖書の原則によって良心を訓練し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.46,0:05:48.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,規則集なしに良い決定を\Nすることができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.17,0:05:56.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,“理性”を働かせることを \N盲導犬と比較することができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.67,0:06:02.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,特に訓練されていない犬でも\N視覚障害者にとって助けになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.45,0:06:05.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば 何かがあれば吠えるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.05,0:06:11.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 特別に訓練された盲動犬は\N驚くほど有能です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.49,0:06:13.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,曲がり角の前で止まったり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.42,0:06:18.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,人がぶつからないよう\N障害物を避けることもします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.63,0:06:24.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,盲導犬は“賢い不服従”と呼ばれる\N特殊な訓練も受けます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.77,0:06:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,視覚障害者が進もうと促しても従わず\N危険を避けようとします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.91,0:06:39.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,盲導犬がそのように有能になるには\N1年かそれ以上の時間が必要です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.58,0:06:46.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,同様に 訓練されていない“理性”も\N幾らか助けにはなります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.72,0:06:52.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 時間をかけて訓練するなら\N驚くべき働きをします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.66,0:06:57.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,では “理性”を訓練するのに役立つ\N3つのスキルを考えましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.03,0:07:04.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,例える 分析する バランスを取るです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.94,0:07:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,最初のスキル 例えることについて\N人を許すというトピックで考えましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.45,0:07:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな聖書の原則によって\N他の人を許すよう助けられますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.26,0:07:24.29,Default2,,0,0,0,,できるだけたくさんの原則や聖句を\N思い浮かべてみてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.29,0:07:26.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして よければビデオをいったん止め—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.66,0:07:29.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,思い浮かんだ原則を\N書き出してみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.34,0:07:41.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,その中には マタイ 18章22節の\N“77回まで”許しなさい や—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.91,0:07:47.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,箴言 12章18節の\N“賢い者たちの舌は人をいやす”—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.92,0:07:53.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,コロサイ 3章13節の“惜しみなく\N許し合いなさい”などがあるでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.56,0:07:57.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,今 学んでいるのは例えること—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.13,0:08:04.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,つまり 心の中で聖句の考えや原則の\N真の意味と要点を思い浮かべる能力です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.50,0:08:10.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,芸術家ではなくても わたしたちは皆\N心の中で思い描くことができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.27,0:08:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えを考えるとき 同じものあるいは\N似たものにするよう心がけてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.02,0:08:27.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば 罪が借金であれば\N許しはそれを帳消しにするものです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.59,0:08:31.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,感情を傷つけることが\N皮膚を切ることならば—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.73,0:08:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,許しはそれを治療することです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.73,0:08:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,罪が黒板に線を引くことなら\N許しはそれを消すことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.81,0:08:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,箴言 12章18節は\N例えに関しての良い手本です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.25,0:08:54.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,“剣で突き刺すかのように\N 無思慮に話す者がいる”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.95,0:08:58.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“しかし 賢い者たちの舌は人をいやす”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.82,0:09:06.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,幼いころ傷つけ 出血した所が\N今どうなっているか考えてみてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.16,0:09:12.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは自然治癒力という\N素晴らしい力を与えてくださいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.14,0:09:19.44,Default2,,0,0,0,,人を許すことによって\N感情的に立ち直っていく様を想像できます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.44,0:09:23.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 例えや想像力を\N時間をかけて訓練しましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.25,0:09:29.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは“理性”を働かせることができる\N最も強力なスキルの一つです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.22,0:09:31.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,それは楽しいものとなります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.62,0:09:35.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,家族の崇拝で\N一つのトピックから原則を考え—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.63,0:09:38.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,どれだけ多くの例えや類似点が\N思いつくか—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.86,0:09:41.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,やってみるのはいかがでしょう？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.66,0:09:49.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それらを発表し合うなら 新たな観点を\N発見できて驚かされるかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.54,0:09:55.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,では次に 2つ目のスキル\N分析することについて考えましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.24,0:09:56.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,分析するとは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.41,0:10:00.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,あるものを“細かいところまで\N注意深く調べる”ことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.62,0:10:05.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,これを間違った欲望という\Nトピックで考えてみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.89,0:10:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,コロサイ 3章5節の原則について\N取り上げてみます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.10,0:10:19.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ですから 淫行 汚れ\N 性的欲情 有害な欲望—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.34,0:10:23.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,“また強欲\N つまり偶像礼拝に関して—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.11,0:10:28.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“地上にあるあなた方の\N 肢体を死んだものとしなさい”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.05,0:10:31.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪い欲望と闘うよう—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.15,0:10:36.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,コロサイ 3章5節を\N分析することから何を学べますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.82,0:10:41.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうしたことを考えるために\N再びビデオを止めてみてください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.89,0:10:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それぞれの段階を注意深く調べましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.56,0:10:53.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,罪に至る段階に\Nどんなことがあるのかお気づきですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.77,0:11:00.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,この聖句は淫行に至る\N根本原因を明らかにしています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.51,0:11:04.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,最後の文から考えましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.31,0:11:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“強欲つまり偶像礼拝”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.25,0:11:15.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,淫行は自己本位 他の何よりも自分の必要に\N貪欲であることから始まります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.79,0:11:18.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,次は “有害な欲望”です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.76,0:11:22.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,“強欲”は“有害な欲望”に至ります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.43,0:11:25.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,お金を払えないのに\Nパン屋の周りで—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.80,0:11:29.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,パンやケーキの匂いを\N嗅ぐことに似ています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.34,0:11:34.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,同様に不道徳な娯楽や悪い交わりは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.24,0:11:39.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちが本来持たないような\N“有害な欲望”をかきたてます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.58,0:11:44.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,次は “性的欲望”です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.39,0:11:49.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,“有害な欲望”は それを満たすことが\N できる機会を探すよう—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.66,0:11:54.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,強い感情的な欲望に変わります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.97,0:11:59.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,続いて “汚れ”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.14,0:12:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,この段階で\N他の人との不適切な関係に至ります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.41,0:12:11.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,最後に重大な罪である“淫行”です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.75,0:12:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,淫行は結婚関係外で起こります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.22,0:12:20.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,コロサイ 3章5節を分析して—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.12,0:12:25.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪い欲望を育てるのではなく\N除くよう助けられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.73,0:12:30.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,それをすぐに捨て去ることの\N重要性も分かります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.37,0:12:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,前の段階であればあるほど\N罪から離れるのは容易になります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.47,0:12:43.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖句をただ読むのではなく\N学んだことを生かして分析しましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.38,0:12:46.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,たくさんの調査用の道具を用いて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.35,0:12:51.99,Default2,,0,0,0,,役立ちそうなコメントや適用を\N見つけることができます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.99,0:12:55.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 最後の3つ目のスキルを\N考えましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.39,0:12:57.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,バランスを取る です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.56,0:13:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,アルコールの用い方という\Nトピックで考えましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.97,0:13:06.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,結婚する2人が披露宴で\Nアルコールを出すかどうかを決める際—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.80,0:13:10.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんな聖書の原則が役立ちますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.81,0:13:17.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,バランスの取れた決定をするため\Nどんな聖句や原則を思い浮かべますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.68,0:13:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,再びビデオを止め 思い浮かんだ原則や\N調べた点を書き出してみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.45,0:13:28.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,挙げられた原則は\N次のようなものかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.96,0:13:33.73,Default2,,0,0,0,,ヨハネ 2章9節でイエスが\N水をぶどう酒に変えられたことです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.73,0:13:37.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかしコリント第一 6章10節には—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.17,0:13:40.74,Default2,,0,0,0,,“大酒飲みは神の王国を受け継がない”\Nともあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.74,0:13:45.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,また コリント第一 10章31, 32節には—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.21,0:13:47.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,“食べるにしても 飲むにしても—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.21,0:13:50.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,“すべての事を\N 神の栄光のためにしなさい” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.41,0:13:54.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,“つまずきのもととならないように”\N ともあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.68,0:13:59.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,たった1つの原則からは\N答えを引き出すことはできないようです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.96,0:14:02.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,2人は “イエスがそうされたんだから—” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.39,0:14:06.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,“披露宴でアルコールを出してもよい”\N と言うかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.06,0:14:08.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 本当にそれだけでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.66,0:14:13.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,バランスを取って\Nすべての原則を考えることが必要です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.54,0:14:18.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,出席者の中に\N酩酊しやすい人がいますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.81,0:14:26.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,地元の習慣や考え方により\N兄弟たちの良心が異なりますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.85,0:14:32.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,決定を下す時は幾つかの原則について\Nバランスを取って考えて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.89,0:14:37.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分に有利な1つの原則だけで\N決定してはなりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.59,0:14:41.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはわたしたちが\N“理性”を働かせ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.36,0:14:46.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,バランスを取って原則を考えて\N決定するよう望んでおられます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.50,0:14:50.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,バランスに関して\N伝道の書 7章16-18節は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.94,0:14:53.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,良い教訓を与えています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.21,0:14:56.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,“義に過ぎる者となってはならない”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.28,0:14:59.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,“また 自分を過度に\N 賢い者としてはならない”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.38,0:15:02.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,“どうして自分の身に\N 荒廃をもたらしてよいであろうか”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.75,0:15:04.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,“邪悪に過ぎる者であってはならない”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.89,0:15:06.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,“また 愚かな者となるな”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.86,0:15:10.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,“自分の時でもないのに\N どうして死んでよいであろうか”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.39,0:15:14.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,“一方をつかむことのほうが良いが\N 他方からも手を引くな”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.06,0:15:18.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,“神を恐れる者はそれらすべてと共に\N 出て行くからである”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.10,0:15:19.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,真理ですね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.64,0:15:21.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書の原則を当てはめる時—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.87,0:15:25.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,対照的な2つの間で\Nバランスを取る必要があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.81,0:15:28.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,いわば 両者に注意を払います\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.81,0:15:31.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,神と隣人への愛を示す決定をするため—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.81,0:15:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,全ての聖書の原則のバランスを\N取る必要があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.49,0:15:40.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,異なる原則に関して\Nバランスを取る点で—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.92,0:15:43.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,この自転車の模型を使って考えましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.69,0:15:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,マラウイの兄弟から頂いた物です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.00,0:15:50.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,自転車は3つの基本要素から\Nなっています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.67,0:15:54.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ブレーキ ペダル ハンドルです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.00,0:16:01.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ブレーキは わたしたちが悪い方向へ\N向かうのを食い止める原則のようです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.24,0:16:09.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,ペダルは神と兄弟姉妹への愛を示すよう\Nわたしたちを動かす原則のようです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.59,0:16:15.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハンドルは エホバを歓ばせる決定を選ぶ\N自由意志のようです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.36,0:16:19.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,決定は自転車に乗るのに似ています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.76,0:16:24.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,幾つかの聖書の原則を\Nバランスを取って考えなければなりません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.40,0:16:27.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,振り返ってみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.60,0:16:32.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは神と隣人への愛という範囲内で\N用いられる自由意志と—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.51,0:16:35.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,多くの聖書の原則を\N与えてくださいました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.81,0:16:39.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,難しい決定をするときには\N“理性”を働かせ—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.25,0:16:42.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,原則を考え 適用しましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.48,0:16:46.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,理性を働かせるのに役立つ\N3つのスキルとは何でしたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.52,0:16:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,例える 分析する バランスを取る です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.13,0:16:53.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,どんなことに直面するとしても—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.86,0:16:55.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,“聖書の原則によって導かれるように”\N していきましょう\N
